verses.roman:
ethā kāśī-miśra āsi' prabhura caraṇe
rājāra caritra saba kailā nivedane

synonyms: ethā—here; kāśī-miśra—Kāśī Miśra; āsi'-coming; prabhura—of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; caraṇe—to the feet; rājāra—of the King; caritra saba—all the behavior; kailā nivedane—informed.
translation: Kāśī Miśra went to Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu and informed Him in detail of all the King's intentions.
